            <p class="lead fs-5 fw-normal">India is a diverse country with 28 states and 8 union territories. Each state has its own distinct culture, language, cuisine, and traditions. Here are some key facts about Indian states.</p>

            <h2 class="hed">Indian States:</h2>
            <ul>
                
                <li><b>Andhra Pradesh:</b> Known for its rich history, beautiful coastline, and traditional arts and crafts.</li>
                <li><b>Arunachal Pradesh:</b> A land of picturesque landscapes, home to diverse indigenous tribes and abundant wildlife.</li>
                <li><b>Assam:</b> Famous for its tea gardens, lush green landscapes, and the mighty Brahmaputra River.</li>
                <li><b>Bihar:</b> The land of ancient ruins and cultural heritage, with a mix of historical sites and religious significance.</li>
                <li><b>Chhattisgarh:</b> Known for its dense forests, tribal culture, and unique wildlife.</li>
                <li><b>Goa:</b> A popular tourist destination with beautiful beaches, vibrant nightlife, and Portuguese influence.</li>
                <li><b>Gujarat:</b> Home to vibrant festivals, intricate handicrafts, and the architectural marvels of ancient civilizations.</li>
                <li><b>Haryana:</b> Known for its agricultural prosperity, rich history, and traditional folk culture.</li>
                <li><b>Himachal Pradesh:</b> A paradise for nature lovers, offering stunning mountains, serene landscapes, and adventure sports.</li>
                <li><b>Jharkhand:</b> Abundant in natural resources, known for its waterfalls, wildlife, and tribal culture.</li>
                <li><b>Karnataka:</b> Famous for its IT industry, historical sites, and diverse cuisine.</li>

            </ul>
