            <ul>

                <li><b>Kerala:</b> Known as "God's Own Country," renowned for its backwaters, Ayurvedic treatments, and lush greenery.</li>
                <li><b>Madhya Pradesh:</b> A treasure trove of ancient monuments, wildlife sanctuaries, and architectural wonders.</li>
                <li><b>Maharashtra:</b> Home to Bollywood, bustling cities, and the iconic Gateway of India.</li>
                <li><b>Manipur:</b> Known for its rich cultural heritage, traditional dance forms, and natural beauty.</li>
                <li><b>Meghalaya:</b> Famous for its living root bridges, breathtaking waterfalls, and misty landscapes.</li>
                <li><b>Mizoram:</b> A state with a distinct identity, known for its picturesque valleys, traditional festivals, and handicrafts.</li>
                <li><b>Nagaland:</b> Home to diverse indigenous tribes, famous for its Hornbill Festival and scenic beauty.</li>
                <li><b>Odisha:</b> Renowned for its ancient temples, pristine beaches, and classical dance forms.</li>
                <li><b>Punjab:</b> Known for its vibrant culture, agricultural prosperity, and lip-smacking cuisine.</li>
                <li><b>Rajasthan:</b> The land of palaces and forts, famous for its rich history, colorful festivals, and desert landscapes.</li>
                <li><b>Sikkim:</b> A state of picturesque beauty, with snow-capped mountains, Buddhist monasteries, and adventure tourism.</li>
                <li><b>Tamil Nadu:</b> Famous for its classical music, stunning temples, and the cultural hub of Chennai.</li>
                <li><b>Telangana:</b> Known for its historical sites, delicious cuisine, and the thriving city of Hyderabad.</li>
                <li><b>Tripura:</b> Famous for its lush green valleys, beautiful lakes, and rich cultural heritage.</li>
                <li><b>Uttar Pradesh:</b> Home to the iconic Taj Mahal, bustling cities, and a mix of cultures and traditions.</li>
                <li><b>Uttarakhand:</b> A paradise for adventure enthusiasts, with breathtaking Himalayan views, pilgrimage sites, and wildlife sanctuaries.</li>
                <li><b>West Bengal:</b> Known for its literary heritage, art, and cultural festivals, and the bustling city of Kolkata.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="hed">Territories Capitals:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Andaman and Nicobar Islands:</b> A group of islands known for their pristine beaches, diverse marine life, and tropical rainforests.</li>
                <li><b>Chandigarh:</b> A well-planned city serving as the capital of both Punjab and Haryana, known for its modern architecture and urban design.</li>
                <li><b>Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Daman and Diu:</b> A union territory formed by the merger of Dadra and Nagar Haveli with Daman and Diu, offering a mix of natural beauty, colonial architecture, and historical significance.</li>
                <li><b>Lakshadweep:</b> A group of coral islands in the Arabian Sea, known for its crystal-clear waters, coral reefs, and vibrant marine life.</li>
                <li><b>Delhi:</b> The national capital territory of India, known for its historical landmarks, bustling markets, and diverse culture.</li>
                <li><b>Puducherry:</b> A former French colony on the southeastern coast of India, famous for its charming colonial architecture, serene beaches, and spiritual atmosphere.</li>
                <li><b>Jammu and Kashmir:</b> A union territory formed after the reorganization of the state of Jammu and Kashmir, known for its stunning Himalayan landscapes, picturesque lakes, and rich cultural heritage.</li>
                <li><b>Ladakh:</b> An Indian territory nestled in the Himalayas, is renowned for its breathtaking landscapes, high-altitude desert, and rich Tibetan Buddhist heritage.</li>
            </ul>
